SIMPLE: onset
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Onset
<hw>On"set`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>On</ets> +
<ets>set</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A rushing or setting upon; an
attack; an assault; a storming; especially, the assault of an
army.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>onset</qex> and retire⟦br⟧
Of both your armies.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who on that day the word of <qex>onset</qex> gave.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A setting about; a beginning; -- used especially of
diseases or pathological symptoms.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is surely no greater wisdom than well to time the beginnings
and <qex>onsets</qex> of things.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything set on, or added, as an ornament or as a
useful appendage.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Onset</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Onset
<hw>On"set`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To assault; to set
upon.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To set about; to begin.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Carew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>onshore</ent>⟦br⟧
